⚔️Ghosts,
 
Welcome to The Grid--your training room for the Winter. Activity here is undetectable by Central Power. Opportunity: infinite. The more you train, the more you'll gain. Take a look around, and when you're ready,
 
let the [Training] begin.
 
https://t.co/FTcWNa1BYV https://t.co/dIpsZHPScr

⚔️--The Grid--
A Resistance-accessible meta-location accessible only to the regiments.
 
"It's been a while, old friend. The Central Power has gotten quite strong! To beat them, we'll need more than strength & endurance; we'll need [Intelligence].
 
Many showed. It's time."

⚔️I find the nearest entry point.
"The city's gotten quite advanced.
Never thought I'd "jump" from reality to reality, like that 1999 movie 'The Matrix' or that book 'Ready Player something,' but here we are: this token The Resistance gave us Ghosts is quite the technology."

⚔️"Sasuka, Saitama,…Luffy--leaders of legends I grew up with underwent rigorous trial to become the heroes they were. Because of them, I know we cannot change the world without [Strength] of mind & body.
 
-Wait-
 
A message arrives:
 
'Ghosts...it's time.'"

⚔️"It's called a battle, because you have to fight for it. It's not supposed to come easy. With each passing day and each passing night, I see some wane in their faith. [Endurance] is the first attribute a Ghost must build. As new recruits choose this path, this they must learn."

⚔️“I believe we all experience many deaths throughout our lives; not only one at the end. The day I said goodbye to the version of me okay with serving the former web for so long, I swore to devote my life fighting for a future we could all own. 'Til that day arrives, I train."

9/ It is known she is out there still, watching, always watching. You would be wise to draw your curtains close, keep your key in the door, for you never know who else watches from the shadows.

8/ When one such victim of Kira’s deeds sent men to find her and ‘bring her in’, like all good Watchers Kira slipped into the shadows, never to be found again - a Watcher hero if ever there was one, doing her duty for society and her Faction.
7/ Many a scandal was ended, or caused, from what Kira saw through those keyholes, private worlds exposed for all to see and hear.
6/ She was not one for blackmail, no, but there was a healthy demand for information on the Watcher black market, and she sold the secrets from her vault for a handsome price.
5/ Kira was a girl who saw secrets through a keyhole, for whom every nook and cranny was a chance to escape from the world and dive into that of another’s.
4/ Nobody really noticed Kira, an ashen-faced teen of surprising insignificance, until she became known to the youths in the town as the ‘keeper of secrets’.

3/ Kira longed to grow older and take her place amongst the Watcher ranks in that grand Tower. She worked hard everyday to improve her observation skills so that she too might be a famous member of the Faction.

2/ Kira didn’t have a stable home, her parents were distant, their minds long since lost to the opiate sticks that many of the city populace smoked into addiction, and they did not have much time for the girl.

7/ When whispers of the rebellion grew, Alvin decided to enlist in the Resistance, the first of the Slums to do so, and thus with this noble act, set himself on the path to legend-hood.
6/ To the underhive gangers who fought for control of the streets and alleys, he was ‘Alvin Rockhard’.

5/ Life was a constant struggle for Alvin, but somehow, he survived into adolescence. His temperament was one of vigilance, with bouts of impulsiveness. He grew lean and agile and was famous for his street fighting capabilities.

4/ Filled with nutrients, this moss was a staple food source for the inhabitants of The Sink, and for those who could not afford the inflated prices of meat from the Rat Trap Gang, more often the only thing that kept them alive.
3/ Orphaned before his 5th birthday, Alvin scratched a living selling cultivated moss that grew on the rocks by the flooded sinkhole from where his district got its name.

2/ Alvin had a rough upbringing - his mother died some days after his birth, and his father, who was never suited to the role, died fighting in the Unity Wars that ravaged the territorial districts of the Slums for many years.
